## How this site is built

The site itself is part of the point, so here's how it works. It runs on
**Next.js 16** with the App Router, and posts are managed with a git-based CMS.
That means:

- Every post is a Markdown file committed to the repo
- Full version history on each post, for free
- No database, no external service, no monthly bill

Editing happens in a clean admin UI, but the output is just files:

```bash
# A new post is literally a new folder + markdown file
src/content/posts/my-new-post/index.mdoc
```

Cheap, fast, and fully under my control — exactly the kind of setup I'd
recommend to anyone trying to do more without adding cost.

